## Form Patterns

### Search/Filter Input

Use `aria-label` for search inputs, NOT `placeholder`:

```json
{
  "type": "interactive",
  "action": "formfill",
  "reftarget": "[aria-label=\"Search [description]\"]",
  "targetvalue": "[search term]",
  "content": "In the search box, type **[term]** to filter the results."
}
```

### Text Input Fields

```json
{
  "type": "interactive",
  "action": "formfill",
  "reftarget": "[aria-label=\"[Field label]\"]",
  "targetvalue": "[value]",
  "content": "Enter **[value]** in the [field name] field."
}
```

---

## Button Patterns

| Scenario | Action | Selector |
|----------|--------|----------|
| Button with `data-testid` | `highlight` | `[data-testid="[value]"]` |
| Button with stable text | `button` | Button text (e.g., `"Install"`) |
| Icon-only button | `highlight` | `[aria-label="[description]"]` |

---

## Integration Setup Patterns

### Alloy Installation Expand Button

```json
{
  "type": "interactive",
  "action": "highlight",
  "reftarget": "[data-testid=\"agent-config-button\"]",
  "content": "Click **Run Grafana Alloy** to expand the installation options."
}
```

### Token Creation → Use Markdown

Token dialogs have multiple paths (create new vs use existing). Use `markdown` since you can't predict the user's choice.

### Test Connection → Use Markdown

Conditional on real-world installation completing first.

